# Hunt 04 — Data Exfiltration Detection

**MITRE ATT&CK:** T1041 — Exfiltration Over C2 Channel  
**Dataset:** Malware Traffic Analysis (PCAP)  
**Analyst:** Ilyas Hodaiby  
**Status:** 

---

## Hypothesis

> After establishing a C2 channel, an attacker will attempt to exfiltrate collected data back to their infrastructure. This produces anomalous outbound traffic patterns — large data volumes to unusual destinations on non-standard ports — detectable through network log analysis.

---

## Log Sources Analysed

| Source | Events | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Network flow logs | Zeek conn.log | Connection metadata |
| PCAP files | Wireshark | Packet-level analysis |
| Windows Security | EventCode 4663 | File access before exfil |
| DNS logs | Zeek dns.log | C2 domain lookups |

